  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "A1. CBSP Groups know and use  available varieties and technologies\r\n\t\r\n\t\tA2. Poor and disadvantaged households have increased access to quality maize seed and proven technologies\r\n\t\r\n\t\tA3. CBSP groups/Cooperatives supply quality seeds at competitive market price\r\n\t\r\n\t\tA4. Poor and disadvantaged maize producing HHs have access to multiple agricultural interventions  for enhanced productivity\r\n\t\r\n\t\tB.1  National Seed Board ( NSB), NARC, DoA allow decentralized source seed production system\r\n\t\r\n\t\tB.2 Public and private institutions obtain seed inspection mandate and license\r\n\t\r\n\t\tB.3  CBSP/cooperatives manage  supply of quality seed\r\n\t\r\n\t\tB.4 NSB and NARC consider HMRP’s experience in variety development, certification and release system"
    },
